ExifTool
Read and write metadata in files

Forensics
Description
ExifTool is a platform-independent tool for reading, writing, and editing metadata in a wide variety of files including images, audio, and video.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which exiftool
Install command:

sudo apt install libimage-exiftool-perl
Basic Syntax
exiftool [options] <file>
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
exiftool image.jpg

Show all metadata	View image info	
exiftool -gps* image.jpg

GPS data only	Find location	
exiftool -all= image.jpg

Remove all metadata	Sanitize image	
exiftool -r -ext jpg directory/

Recursive on JPGs	Batch processing	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Run exiftool on file
2
Review metadata
3
Check GPS for location
4
Note camera/device info
5
Remove if needed
Understanding the Output
Shows all embedded metadata including camera, date, location, and software info.

Important Warnings
•
Metadata can reveal sensitive info
•
Always check before sharing files
•
GPS data can expose location
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
